    'Episodes Summary': '<p>Cloud Foundry is an open-source platform as a service. Companies use Cloud Foundry as a control plane to deploy and manage applications. It provides abstractions for microservices and continuous integration. </p><p>Cornelia Davis joins the show to discuss Cloud Foundry. I interviewed her at the DevOps Enterprise Summit, where enterprises share their stories of improving their culture and their technology stack. Cornelia explained how and why a large enterprise adopts Cloud Foundry, and why they often hire a company like Pivotal to help them as they migrate their infrastructure and change their processes.</p>',
