    'Episodes Pubdate Date': '2016-10-06',
    'Episodes Summary': '<p>Scala is a functional programming language built on the JVM. For more than a decade, this didn’t mean anything to front end web developers. More recently, ScalaJS has brought Scala to the front end. ScalaJS is a project that compiles any Scala program down to JavaScript–so that all of your Scala programs can run on the browser.</p><p>Haoyi Li has worked on ScalaJS extensively and has written an online book about ScalaJS. If you are a front end developer looking for a safer way to write your web apps, you will like this episode–or if you are a fan of functional programming.</p>',
