    'Episodes Summary': '<p>Tessel is an open-source microcontroller that is programmable in JavaScript and compatible with Node.js.</p><p>Kelsey Breseman is a hardware engineer and Steering Committee Member on the Tessel Project.</p><p><a href="http://www.hired.com/softwareengineeringdaily">Hired.com</a> is the job marketplace for software engineers. Go to <a href="http://www.hired.com/softwareengineeringdaily">hired.com/softwareengineeringdaily</a> to get a <strong>$600 bonus</strong> upon landing a job through Hired.</p><p><a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/?utm_medium=podcasts&amp;utm_source=sedaily&amp;utm_campaign=sedaily">Digital Ocean</a> is the simplest cloud hosting provider. Use promo code SEDAILY for $10 in free credit.</p>',
