    'Episodes Summary': '<p>Git is the most popular version control system. If you have been programming for less than a decade, it’s likely that you haven’t used any other method of version control. The git workflow of a software team defines how that team collaborates, builds, and ships software.</p><p>Tim Pettersen is a developer advocate at Atlassian, where he has been building software around git for many years. He joins us on today’s episode to talk about strategies for git–including branching, merging, continuous integration, and software as a service.</p>',
