    'Episodes Pubdate Date': '2016-08-03',
    'Episodes Summary': '<p>Odd Networks is building a platform for anyone to launch their own over-the-top streaming video service. With Odd Networks, you can deploy your own video channel using a Roku, Amazon Fire TV, Apple TV, and other services.</p><p><br>\nCreating a streaming video service with interoperability between these different platforms presents numerous technical challenges, and today’s guest Kris Walker explains how Odd Networks is addressing those challenges. We discuss the open source projects of Odd Networks, including oddworks, which encompases the SDKs, stores, services, and middleware, and the event bus, called oddcast.Sponsors</p>',
