    'Episodes Summary': '<p>A content management system (CMS) defines how the content on a website is arranged and presented. The most widely used CMS is WordPress, the open source tool that is written in PHP. A large percentage of the web consists of WordPress sites, and WordPress has a huge ecosystem of plugins and templates.</p><p>Despite the success of WordPress, the JAMStack represents the future of web development. JAM stands for JavaScript, APIs, and Markup. In contrast to the monolithic WordPress  deployments, a JAMStack site consists of loosely coupled components. And there are numerous options for a CMS in this environment.</p><p>TinaCMS is one such option. TinaCMS is an acronym for “Tina Is Not A CMS”, and it is a toolkit for content management. Scott Gallant, Jordan Patterson, and Nolan Phillips work on TinaCMS, and they join the show to explore the topic of content management on the JAMStack.</p>',
