    'Episodes Summary': '<p>DevOps has been the subject of many episodes of Software Engineering Daily. And yet–the question we continue to ask ourselves is “what is DevOps?”  In order to understand the present, we must look into the past. On today’s show, we break down the history of dev ops with Demir Selmanovic, the lead technical editor at TopTal.</p><p>From waterfall software development, to the agile manifesto. From lean manufacturing to the productive pinnacle of DevOps nirvana. Demir also wrote a blog post called <a href="https://www.toptal.com/devops/what-the-hell-is-devops">What the Hell is DevOps</a>, which he posted on the TopTal blog. Full disclosure: TopTal is a sponsor of our show, but this episode doesn’t discuss TopTal very much so hopefully that doesn’t impact the trust of our listeners.</p>',
