    'Episodes Pubdate Date': '2016-02-10',
    'Episodes Summary': '<p>You keep hearing about containers, and maybe you have even used Docker in production. Now, it’s time to move beyond Docker. In today’s episode of Software Engineering Daily, Steve Pousty talks about OpenShift, a platform from RedHat that helps engineers leverage the power of containers and the dev ops harmony of microservices.</p><p>To hear these buzzwords, you can always listen to Software Engineering Daily. But to see these buzzwords demonstrated in live presentations, the 2016 O’Reilly Fluent Conference is coming up March 8-10 in San Francisco, and you can get a chance to win a free ticket by tweeting at us about your favorite episode of Software Engineering Daily. Include the hashtag #fluentconf and and tag us @software_daily to make sure we can see your tweet.</p><p>Steve Pousty is a Developer Advocate (and PaaS Dust Spreader) at Red Hat.</p>',
