    'Episodes Summary': '<p>Building a monitoring system is a complex distributed systems problem. Events are produced from different points in an application and must be aggregated in order to form metrics. These events are often ingested by a time series database, which forms the backbone of our monitoring system.</p><p>Theo Schlossnagle is the CEO of Circonus, where he has been working on architecting the company’s monitoring software for six years. In this episode, we talk about how to build a monitoring system and the requirements for the underlying time-series database, as well as what monitoring even is.</p>',
